\begin_layout Standard
Status consumption was notably elaborated by Veblen 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "VeblenLeisureClass"
literal "true"

\end_inset

 in his 1899 treatise titled 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Theory of the Leisure Class
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 Around the time when Marx had endorsed a view of all commodities as products
 of labour (diamond and corn alike), Veblen seems interested in the psychologica
l basis for consumption among the economic classes.
 At times his view of status consumption may appear critical of the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

bourgeois
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 wastefulness 
