 In terms of our model, it is only the former costs for assets - as well
 as from the costs of basic internal needs - that is absolutely necessary
 for one's social reference group.
 Thus we can say that the peer effects influence the consumer's choice of
 excess relative to asset-band 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathscr{A}$
\end_inset


\series bold
 
\series default
and that the external needs of the consumer's reference group comprise both
 of costs associated with 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathscr{A}$
\end_inset

 and the excess
